The paper deals with the problem of sensor scheduling for remote state estimation of multiple processes, which involves topics related to control systems (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.AI). The proposed method also involves stochastic processes and optimization, which are relevant to the categories of mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
